      "(0.9961, 'I am an South African, who lived in the USA 2000 to 2006 and now an Australian, still living in Australia.\\nAll 3 countries have negative gearing.   \\nI know a lot of people hype negative gearing is the cause and attraction for high prices, it is not.  Yes it is in part, but In my view plays a very small part in it.\\nWhy would I incur a huge amount of cost to me, just to knock off 5 or less % on my overall tax?  \\nIt makes no sense.   You are happy to pay 95% cost to get 5% back from the gov in tax.  \\nYou are better off saving the costs and pay your tax, unless you can get an invesment which is high growth, and make a buck from it, regardless of the cost.\\n\\nThe bigger cause for Australian property is the law makes who have no idea about industry and business.  Some do, but they are minority parties.\\nThe big 2 parties are all about appeasing the people and controlling them.\\nSince the 1990s, Australian governments are happier to slap more regulations, and hamper industry growth than to protect or help industry and commerce grow.\\nThey are happy to let foreigners come in and own businesses and industry, than protect locals.\\nThe what when was a manufacturing, minining and commerce economy, today is more tech and commerce with mining on the side.   Manufacturing got outsourced.\\nSo of course, the general enconomy is weak, making the Ozzie Dollar weaker too, and faster rising prices of everything, including the biggest invetments like property.\\n\\nTo help with struggling economy, the gov thought it good to keep interest rates low.  \\nTo allow literallty thousands if not a million or 2 in foreign students to come \"study\" here, to prevent Universities and Colleges from total collapse.\\nBut nowhere di the gov help or mandate where these students will live.  \\nMost tertiary education place have zero on site dormatories or similar student housing, unlike in the US and South Africa for example.\\nSo these students have to \"rent\" regular homes and apartments, which pushes up rental demand around these institutions.\\n\\nIn addtion,  Australia has an active migration program, encouraging people to come live here.   Again to \"stimulate\" economic activity and help with \"labour\" shortages.\\nAnd where do these have to stay?\\nEven a house in the middle of nowhere is prohibitively expensive.\\n\\nTHe gov made 1st home buyers policies and encouraging and allowing 1st home buyers in their 20s to buy at 95% LVR or worse, and cover their bank insurance.   Yet the houses are so expensive, if the interest rate just rises by a small margin these people would be in trouble.\\nEffectively it is not these people who own the property,  it is the bank.\\n\\nTHe central bank has no control over the commercial banks, unlike in RSA for example where interest rates has to be within X basis points of the Central bank.\\nSimilarly goes for central control of certain basic commonodies, like energy, fuel etc.   Gov has no control of any of it, and the semi gov  companies who run the show can ask what they want.\\n\\nAustralia also allow auctions and in fact most properties are sold at auction, whereas in RSA and US, most properties are sold off set price or private negotiated deals, among parties.\\nWith auctions, there is the wild bidding wars, allowing the vendor to get the highest price, and because so many need a place to stay,  auctions are popular.\\n\\nOther thing is gov don\\'t build high density low income housing or housing estates anymore.  And the ones which were, were sold and are not anymore gov housing estates.\\nLow or no income people, need a place to stay, and that is what those are for.   People living these are tenants, or long term leases, they should never allow a property to be sold outright.\\n\\nI say ban auctions completely.  Only use it for deceased estate!.   \\nCrank up the interest rate, and shake out those who can\\'t afford.\\nInstitute a cap on how much can be borrowed,  e.g. no more than 60%.\\nBan or restict foreign investment in property/land/mining., unless certain conditions are true.')\n",
      "(0.9961, 'I am an South African, who lived in the USA 2000 to 2006 and now an Australian, still living in Australia.\\nAll 3 countries have negative gearing.   \\nI know a lot of people hype negative gearing is the cause and attraction for high prices, it is not.  Yes it is in part, but In my view plays a very small part in it.\\nWhy would I incur a huge amount of cost to me, just to knock off 5 or less % on my overall tax?  \\nIt makes no sense.   You are happy to pay 95% cost to get 5% back from the gov in tax.  \\nYou are better off saving the costs and pay your tax, unless you can get an invesment which is high growth, and make a buck from it, regardless of the cost.\\n\\nThe bigger cause for Australian property is the law makes who have no idea about industry and business.  Some do, but they are minority parties.\\nThe big 2 parties are all about appeasing the people and controlling them.\\nSince the 1990s, Australian governments are happier to slap more regulations, and hamper industry growth than to protect or help industry and commerce grow.\\nThey are happy to let foreigners come in and own businesses and industry, than protect locals.\\nThe what when was a manufacturing, minining and commerce economy, today is more tech and commerce with mining on the side.   Manufacturing got outsourced.\\nSo of course, the general enconomy is weak, making the Ozzie Dollar weaker too, and faster rising prices of everything, including the biggest invetments like property.\\n\\nTo help with struggling economy, the gov thought it good to keep interest rates low.  \\nTo allow literallty thousands if not a million or 2 in foreign students to come \"study\" here, to prevent Universities and Colleges from total collapse.\\nBut nowhere di the gov help or mandate where these students will live.  \\nMost tertiary education place have zero on site dormatories or similar student housing, unlike in the US and South Africa for example.\\nSo these students have to \"rent\" regular homes and apartments, which pushes up rental demand around these institutions.\\n\\nIn addtion,  Australia has an active migration program, encouraging people to come live here.   Again to \"stimulate\" economic activity and help with \"labour\" shortages.\\nAnd where do these have to stay?\\nEven a house in the middle of nowhere is prohibitively expensive.\\n\\nTHe gov made 1st home buyers policies and encouraging and allowing 1st home buyers in their 20s to buy at 95% LVR or worse, and cover their bank insurance.   Yet the houses are so expensive, if the interest rate just rises by a small margin these people would be in trouble.\\nEffectively it is not these people who own the property,  it is the bank.\\n\\nTHe central bank has no control over the commercial banks, unlike in RSA for example where interest rates has to be within X basis points of the Central bank.\\nSimilarly goes for central control of certain basic commonodies, like energy, fuel etc.   Gov has no control of any of it, and the semi gov  companies who run the show can ask what they want.\\n\\nAustralia also allow auctions and in fact most properties are sold at auction, whereas in RSA and US, most properties are sold off set price or private negotiated deals, among parties.\\nWith auctions, there is the wild bidding wars, allowing the vendor to get the highest price, and because so many need a place to stay,  auctions are popular.\\n\\nOther thing is gov don\\'t build high density low income housing or housing estates anymore.  And the ones which were, were sold and are not anymore gov housing estates.\\nLow or no income people, need a place to stay, and that is what those are for.   People living these are tenants, or long term leases, they should never allow a property to be sold outright.\\n\\nI say ban auctions completely.  Only use it for deceased estate!.   \\nCrank up the interest rate, and shake out those who can\\'t afford.\\nInstitute a cap on how much can be borrowed,  e.g. no more than 60%.\\nBan or restict foreign investment in property/land/mining., unless certain conditions are true.')\n",
      "(0.9925, 'Australia is one of only two countries where the bank can change your interest rate after you have taken out a mortgage in the others your mortgage rate remains the same for the entirety of the loan.\\n\\nI am advocating to everyone that at the next federal election no one votes for either major party as we need to get our power back and that can only be done with a hung parliament.\\n\\nI  am finding it stunning that with the Liberal party being decimated they are not even talking about fixing this situation and so many others.\\n\\nWe need to go back to the model that made the boomers wealthy and grew our middle class which was to increase the size of the public service ie for the government to stop outsourcing everything to their mates driving up the cost and increasing insecure employment as most of those employed are contractors.  But go back to having things such as employment services being completely done by the government and not the $64 B job service providers who provide nothing for that money. Bring back water, gas, electricity and all tolls to the government their can still be private sector suppliers but the government will now also be one this will reintroduce true competition in these areas and return all areas social housing to the government getting rid of all the private sector interests causing a rise in costs.  All of this will increase the number of long term secure employment which results in spending which increases employment.  Additionally we need to raise the rate of government support payments so that people cannot be exploited ie I better not loose my job or I will be destitute.  It  is more expensive to have it at a low level as it puts financial barriers between people and employment where as at a higher rate they are removed the money is spent locally putting it back into the economy whilst increasing jobs.  We then need to reintroduce recommended retail prices being on all consumable goods this meant that businesses could make a profit but could not price gouge ad their was a known price set that was the most they could charge for an item.  Final we need to make university education free again so that people can be competitive on the job market and not weighed down by debt we need to be encouraging people to be educated not discouraging them as we want Australia to lead the world.')\n",
