      "(0.989, 'When l went to Australia for the 3rd time the plane flew over Melbourne. Goodness, vast stretches of homes cluttered next to eachother. Some with blue water pools & cars parked in open fields. Is this what life has to offer us in our life time? I  work for a brand new car, 2 years bank loan. After that experience l thought to myself, Lord is this my purpose for living, paying car loan for 24 months? Times drag, but finance just clear my cheques as l left 24 pieces of signed cheques to that finance Co. Then l started working my account on Housing loans, compounding interest. Just for two years, l realise it works out too costly. Cheaper to rent while.  I save enough to pay in full for a small house outside of town. But it\\'s almost 20 years l paid cash for this home  & that \"town\" has now moved to exactly where l live. Government offices, Shopping Centre, Most people love to go for fishing  & boating.  It\\'s never a lonely for an Octogenarian like me. So buying a home is one thing.  Make sure convience is walking distance as it\\'s an aging society & one needs to be independent. Enjoy your retirement with the little help from the government & minimum savings. Don\\'t forget the Lord. Walk to church, a short distance. It\\'s life.')\n"
