      "(-0.9957, 'bruh ketamine is one of the most important medicines ever made, its basically one of the only non-gas drugs that can be used similarly to gas anesthetics when putting people under in places with minimal infrastructure, like the third world or in emergency scenarios, even with gasses ket is still sometimes used as one of the anesthetics in surgery, it also is a heavily researched treatment for depression, and if you want to ban ket, then the third world might actually start doing surgery with fucking pcp again which is the drug that ket replaced.\\n\\nAlso the only differences in the effects between GHB and alcohol is basically the dosage curve, instead a few ml will get you to the same place several shots do, it acts on the same neurons, and has extremely similar reported effects. But you are right, GHB has little to no medical value, it does have value as a chemical solvent which is the reason it used to be found in Legos and other plastic items, and after it was found to get people high, people stopped using it in products that could be swallowed before the law was even in place, and after it was in place, it just became harder to use it as a solvent and more people found out that it could be used as a drug.\\n\\nAlso to anyone that wants to yell about me relating GHB and alcohol, THERE IS A REASON IT IS A DATE RAPE DRUG, because it feels the exact same as the most used date rape drug.... WHICH IS LITERALLY JUST ALCOHOL (mostly in cocktails so the victim doesn\\'t realize how much they drank), and it got headlines because of how similar they would feel, leaving the victim only conscious that they have been drugged after its too late (because again, its basically the same effects).\\n\\nThe dosage curve for GHB is also notable because it shows that your body absorbs much more of it, making a proper equivalent (effects wise) dose of GHB being less toxic than alcohol, as not only is the alcohol killing your cells, but also the illegal chemicals that are also alcohol metabolites (which can be less toxic than the alcohol), are also still toxic, making an equivalent dose of GHB the \"healthier\" option, all tho due to the nature and difficulty of dosing GHB due to a logarithmic style dosage curve its near impossible to dose GHB properly.\\nSo the only significant danger, while being significant enough that most people shouldnt do it as they put themselves at grater risk for overdose, is only the wild nature of dosing, not toxicity, or effects (unless you wanna start shutting bars/clubs/alcohol vendors down for selling a substance that can cause people to have increased aggression). \\n\\nPlease stop demonizing drugs, and yes I know I made a wall of text for a joke but addiction is fucking painful and the more people misrepresent the arguments, jokes or not, the more damage it ends up doing for users who are only really scared of getting help because people still treat us like shit, making these kinds of jokes to our faces.\\nWe all know the drugs we do are unhealthy, we dont need it repeated, we need treatment, the real joke is how completely ignorant most countries are to modern addiction research.\\n\\nTL:DR\\nDrug rant sourced by MAPS, John Hopkins uni, some chemical discussions, Harvard medicine, and many many more universities, that all basically conclude in \"modern addiction policy makes more victims of an induced substance abuse cycle, and actual treatment looks the exact same as treating any other mental health condition. We don\\'t put people in jail for depression, we shouldn\\'t put people in jail for addiction.\"')\n",
      "(-0.9938, 'Come on mate. The 5% is a fucking ridiculous idea that\\'s pushing up prices. As has been stated by most economists.\\n\\nYes Labor is doing a better job than whoever the fuck else we could\\'ve gotten. But seriously take a breath cunt. Things aren\\'t good. It\\'s okay to admit that.\\n\\nWhere\\'s all the land coming from?\\nOh that\\'s right we\\'re just going to let all these new developments push further into farm lands or flood plains. Nah dont worry cunt not like there\\'s growing climate instability. Not like jobs exist in the city that you\\'re being pushed further away from. \\n\\nwhere\\'s all the labour coming from?\\n\\nYou even spruked the unions, and I like unions. But you know what else unions do? Implement artificial restrictions on labour in order to get a wage rise.\\n\\n Think I\\'m wrong? Wasn\\'t it Labor policy to promote \"white Australia\"?\\n\\nYou\\'ve got red tape and regulations. Do you know how many fucking hoops you have to jump through to get a building certified? \\n\\nMaterials shortages. And on top of that environmental impacts of continued material use. You know concrete and steel are carbon intensive industry right?\\n\\nAnd this is just the critique of some dumb cunt on YouTube. We get it you like Labor you like Albanese.  It fuck sake mate how about you just admit that. Always bagging everyone because they\\'re too stupid to comprehend the greatness of Labor\\'s unqestionable genius.\\n\\nThey\\'ve had plenty of fucked takes. The EPA and cowering to WA gas barrons, this fucking gutless facade of an ICAC, Gaza. \\n\\nThey\\'re sitting on a free ticket to reform. Between the greens, the cross bench and the coalition they could basically pass whatever law they wanted right now. So what do they do? An economic round table to rehash old ideas no one cared about the first time and ignore the elephant in the room which is an outdated taxation system that isn\\'t making sufficient revenue to even pay for current let alone future expenditure.\\n\\nLabor is usually a good choice. Considered and effective policy. But the longer albo sits on his hands banging on about fucking public consensus the longer we have to wait for solutions and momentum.')\n",
      "(-0.9917, 'It really makes me question why I like a fair amount of your other content when you are so mindlessly biased like this.\\n\\nAlbo’s response to the housing crisis and cost of living crisis is anaemic at best but nah, you don’t criticise them. You literally start the video pointing out that you are ‘finally’ addressing this topic. Wonder why you wouldn’t be discussing a massive national crisis sooner? Almost like Labor have done absolutely fuck all but pay for nuclear subs and pass massive tax cuts you haven’t criticised of course.\\n\\nNow that you interact with labor mp’s and people associated with the party a lot more officially, your objectivity is just gone. \\n\\nThere is no way you honestly attack the greens for denying pennies for housing during a unprecedented housing crisis while your cunt of a party passes top heavy tax cuts. \\n\\nAnd again, why the fuck are you spending even a second on the greens? It’s a massive issue so why are you spending time on petty unrelated shit that feels like timid throwing hoping something sticks?\\n\\n\\nCunt, do better hey?')\n",
      "(-0.991, 'Watching that politician fail to explain why deflation is bad was insufferable. I understand the nuance is impossible in a tiktok but the argument of house price collapses facilitating the existing ultra wealthy to suck up the housing stock, force prices back up and make the problem even worse, doesn\\'t take that long to say. The argument of why would it be good to turn houses into a depreciating asset and burden people with bad debt. Housing market collapse would create an economic ripple similar to the 2009 crisis as national debt leverages implode and no one can access liquidity. Like come on. \"You might have an opinion, but my party thinks it would be super duper bad I think.\" - Is the WRONG answer!!')\n",
      "(-0.9903, \"Houses are built for buyers not residents. \\n\\nHOUSING UNAFFORDABILITY PUTS AUSTRALIANS IN ACTUAL DANGER \\n\\nAbused spouses can't afford to escape, let alone with their children. \\nBuying a house should be affordable for a single parent on a modest income.  \\n\\nPeople in share/group-housing are in danger of violence by their other housemates and/or their housemate's partners. \\n\\nPeople are letting their partners illegally live with them in share-housing, which puts the legitimate residents in danger. \\n\\nPeople with abusive parents either have to stay with their abusive parents - using housing to maintain their coercive control - or they'll take up with unsafe people not realising that they're now in a new dangerous situation. Either exploitive housemates or (as my grandmother did) enter into what became an abusive marriage. \\n\\nPlenty of staff in Community Housing service providers (NGOs) are abusive towards their tenants. \\nConstantly threatening eviction to troublesome tenants, ie tenants who put in complaints about staff abusiveness and complaints about lack of repairs. \\nAnd the Community Housing service providers and their staff are going to get their paychecks, so they have zero motivation to properly adhere to their legal and contractual requirements. \\nAnd further, the tenants do not know their rights. They do not know where to direct their complaints so that changes in behaviour is actually undergone. \\nAND IF any contractor thinks it's okay to up the bills given to publicly funded NGO community housing service providers because it's the government paying the bill - SORRY, BUT YOU'RE WRONG - those costs are passed on as much as possible to the tenant stuck in the C'Link just to be able to eat.\")\n",
